housetext:
This large floor-flat of 241sq.m is set on the 3rd floor and is facing one of the largest green areas of Athens' Center, Pedio tou Areos. 
The building dates from 1938 but the specific flat has been fully renovated in 2000. It has kept and maintained some of the original pieces such as the exceptional woodwork, see the various doors' designs and most of the wooden flooring. Bathrooms have been reformed and modernized, all the windows are now double-glazed and various lightnings have been set.
Following the current office use, the kitchen is very small but most of the main rooms in facade have remained the same.
As a home some spaces may open and a large living area with an unhindered view to the Parc would definitely be outstanding.
ACROPOLIS OF ATHENS NOW FOR RENT!!
